               <head>Sa'di's Bustan, abridged</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Kitāb-i Būstān-i Shaykh Saʿdī ʿalayhi al-raḥmah by Saʿdī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100085 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010115018" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_16279-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>An abridgement of Būstān, the renowned didactic masnavī poem by Sa‘dī of Shiraz (d. 691/1292 or 694/1295), apparently completed in 655/1257. The complete text of the Būstān comprises nearly 4,500 couplets, roughly one-third of which appear in this abridgement.</p>
                        <p>In the present manuscript, an additional bayt, which matches neither the poet’s theology nor the poem’s metre, has been inserted after Sa‘dī’s last bayt.</p>
                        <p>On this author and his works see e.g. J. Rypka in Cambridge History of Iran, V, pp. 594-600. For manuscripts of the complete Būstān, see FNKhF IV, pp. 2663-8 (118 manuscripts); but this work cites none under the title Muntakhab-i Būstān; other copies are to be found in manuscripts of Sa‘dī’s Kulliyyāt: see FNKhF III, pp. 1861-70 (144 manuscripts).</p>
                        <p>Another important Muntakhab-i Būstān is in the British Library collection: Or. 14654.</p>
                        <p>Begins: Ba-nām-i Khudāvand-i jān-āfarīn * Ḥakīm-i sukhan dar zabān āfarīn</p>
                        <p>Ends: Baẓā‘at nayāvardam illā umīd * Khudāyā zi ‘avfam makun nā-umīd,
Ya Murtażà ‘Alī bugshā mushkil marā * ham mushkil-i marā bugshā ham dil-marā
</p>
                        <p>Colophon, f. 22v. Copied (in Iran) for Mullā-Bāshī, evidently a leading cleric, by Muḥammad Karīm, who produced the work in advanced old age as a memento and asks to be pardoned for its deficiencies. Dated 18 Zū l-Qa‘da 128, probably signifying 128[0]/25 April 1864. </p>
                        <p>Calligraphic shikasta. Red headings. 20 lines, in two columns, in central panel; about 16 in margin panels. Blue and gold text frames. Illuminated headpiece on f. 1v. Thin off-white paper. 24 folios. 153 x 92 mm.; text area 100 x 45 mm. Limp covers in red morocco.</p>
                        <p>Purchased at Christie’s sale of 28 April 2005, Lot 84.</p>
